arXiv.abstract:
We propose an $S_{4}$ flavor model based on supersymmetric (SUSY) SU(5) GUT. The first and third generations of 	extbf{10} dimensional representations in SU(5) are all assigned to be $1_{1}$ of $S_{4}$. The second generation of 	extbf{10} is to be $1_{2}$ of $S_{4}$. Right-handed neutrinos of singlet 	extbf{1} and three generations of $ ar{	extbf{5}}$ are all assigned to be $3_{1}$ of $S_{4}$. The VEVs of two sets of flavon fields are allowed a moderate hierarchy, that is $\langle\Phi^{
u}angle \sim \lambda_{c}\langle\Phi^{e}angle$. Tri-Bimaximal (TBM) mixing can be produced at both leading order (LO) and next to next to leading order (NNLO) in neutrino sector. All the masses of up-type quarks are obtained at LO. We also get the bottom-tau unification $m_{	au}=m_{b}$ and the popular Georgi-Jarlskog relation $m_{\mu}=3m_{s}$ as well as a new mass relation $m_{e}= rac{8}{27}m_{d}$ in which the novel Clebsch-Gordan (CG) factor arises from the adjoint field $H_{24}$. The GUT relation leads to a sizable mixing angle $	heta^{e}_{12} \sim 	heta_{c}$ and the correct quark mixing matrix $V_{CKM}$ can also be realised in the model. The resulting CKM-like mixing matrix of charged leptons modifies the vanishing $	heta^{
u}_{13}$ in TBM mixing to a large $	heta^{PMNS}_{13}\simeq	heta_{c}/\sqrt{2}$, in excellent agreement with experimental results. A Dirac CP violation phase $\phi_{12}\simeq\pm\pi/2$ is required to make the deviation from $	heta^{
u}_{12}$ small. We also present some phenomenological numerical results predicted by the model.
